                "reviewBody": "Classic!  This is THE method to use for really good mashed potatoes.  It is essential to add salt to the cooking water - oh and start with cool water - bring to temp and then reduce the heat so the water just simmers, not boils.  This way the taters cook evenly.  Thanks for posting this Chef John.",
